## Summary

Implemented T-013: Manual Node Addition with these components:

**AddNodeDropdown** (`src/components/canvas/AddNodeDropdown.tsx`):
- Toolbar button that opens a categorized dropdown menu
- 6 categories (Client, API Layer, Services, Data, Infrastructure, External) with expandable subtypes
- Clicking a subtype creates a new `StackNode` with default values and triggers the detail panel

**ConnectionTypeSelector** (`src/components/canvas/ConnectionTypeSelector.tsx`):
- Positioned popover for selecting connection types when creating edges
- Shows all 6 types (HTTP, WebSocket, gRPC, TCP, Pub/Sub, File I/O) with descriptions
- Closes on outside click or selection

**Project page integration** (`src/app/project/[id]/page.tsx`):
- AddNodeDropdown in toolbar with node count indicator
- New nodes initialize canvasState if empty, appended otherwise
- Detail panel auto-opens for newly added nodes
- Simple card-based node list view (until React Flow arrives in T-009)
- ConnectionTypeSelector wired for pending connections
- Extracted `saveCanvasState` helper to reduce duplication

**Tests**: 17 new tests (10 + 7), all 46 total tests passing. Typecheck and lint clean.

